                            <td>To ensure that accurate information is shared in a timely manner, Ant Commodity works has an intermediary in exchanging information between producer and buyer. </td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td style="width: 30px; padding-left: 10px;"><i class="fa fa-arrows"></i></td>
                            <td>To ensure buyer receives the shipment they agreed to purchase,AntCommodity inspect the shipment before releasing the funds to the producers. </td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td style="width: 30px; padding-left: 10px;"><i class="fa fa-arrows"></i></td>
                            <td>Ant Commodity works with a hardworking, skilled commodity, logistics experts to provide a better service.</td>
                        </tr>
                    </table>
                </div>
                <hr>

                <h3 style="color:#000; font-weight:bold"><a name="shipment">#</a> What if the shipment does not pass inspection byAnt Commodity?</h3>
                <div style="padding-left:25px;;">
                    If the inspection is failed, Ant Commodity will not release the funds to producer
                    nor send the shipment to buyer. Ant Commodity will send the inspection report to producer
                    and buyer at the same time with information about the discrepancies.
                    <br><br>
                    Ant Commodity will coordinate both sides to come to an agreement. If an agreement
                    cannot be reached, AntCommodity will cancel the contract, and will send the full
                    amount excluding bank charges back to buyer.
                </div>
                <hr>

                <h3 style="color:#000; font-weight:bold"><a name="whoShip">#</a> Who is shipping the shipment?</h3>
                <div style="padding-left:25px;;">
                    It is Ant Commodity that send the shipment to the buyer, not the producer.
                    We have a team of experts that understands the international trade very well.
                    <br><br>
                    After Ant Commodity inspects the shipment, pass the inspection and release the funds to
                    buyer, AntCommodity receives temporary ownership of the shipment. This gives no room for
                    the producer to make changes to the shipment before shipping.
                </div>
                <hr>

                <h3 style="color:#000; font-weight:bold"><a name="payment">#</a> What are our payment terms and methods?</h3>
                <div style="padding-left:25px;;">
                    There is no subscription fee, or any other fee for buyers search commodities or interact with
                    producers on Ant Commodity.
                    <br><br>
                    For requests that require a payment of less than $100, AntCommodity will send an online payment
                    to send the payment. For the online payment, there will be a 3.5% bank fee. Ant Commodity
                    must receive the payment in full to execute the service.
                    <br><br>
                    For orders that require a payment of more than $100, AntCommodity will send bank information
                    to send the funds to. This will be a T/T transfer, and there will be a $45 fixed bank fee for
                    each transaction. Ant Commodity must receive the payment in full to execute the service.
                </div>
                <hr>

                <h3 style="color:#000; font-weight:bold"><a name="creditCard">#</a> Is my credit card and bank details safe?</h3>
